-- Czech Stocks: CEZ, Erste Group, Komercni Banka Move in Budapest
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-04-16T16:29:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/czech-stocks-cez-erste-group-bank-komercni-banka-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
fell for a second day to almost a three-month low, dropping 1.2
percent to 919.30 at the close in Prague.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  CEZ AS (CEZ)  , the country’s biggest power producer, slid
2.5 percent to 753.5 koruna. Electricity prices for next-year
delivery in Germany, where the company exports part of its
output, fell 1.2 percent to 51.05 euros per megawatt-hour, a
two-month low.  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS)   of Austria lost 2.3 percent
to 384 koruna while  Komercni Banka AS (KOMB)  , the Czech unit
of Societe Generale SA, dropped 1 percent to 3,561 koruna.
Financial stocks were among the worst performers in  Europe  today
as Spanish bond yields rose to a four-month high, nearing levels
that prompted Greece, Ireland and Portugal to seek bailouts.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
